{
    "ocr_text": "17                                                                 October   . 1909.

Dr. W. G. Prezner,
Post Office General Delivery,
Seattle, Washington.

Dear Sir:-

In acknowledging receipt of your favor of the 12th instant, 
addressed to President Gompers, I beg to advise you that at the 
Executive Council of the American Federation of Labor is in session 
at headquarters this week, his time is wholly engrossed with the 
immediate work of the Council, and therefore is unable to give 
any attention to his correspondence.

You will kindly accept this acknowledgment of receipt 
of your letter until such time he will be able to give the matter 
about which you write his personal attention.

Very truly yours,

P. Lu Grand 
Secretary to President Gompers.",
    "summary": "The letter, dated October 1909, is from P. Lu Grand, the Secretary to President Gompers, to Dr. W. G. Prezner, acknowledging receipt of his letter from the 12th. It informs Dr. Prezner that President Gompers is currently occupied with the Executive Council of the American Federation of Labor and is unable to respond at the moment.",
